&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Energize Your Career:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; At MetOx International, we’re pioneering the next era of energy security and abundance through breakthrough superconducting technology. As a Process Engineering Intern, you’ll join a dynamic team committed to strengthening the world’s energy systems to make them more resilient, efficient, and reliable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at our global headquarters in Houston, TX, MetOx is seeking a motivated fall Process Engineering Intern to join our team. This role offers hands-on experience with production processes, data analysis, and continuous improvement initiatives. You&#39;ll gain exposure to advanced manufacturing techniques and collaborate closely with seasoned engineers on critical projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours between 9am - 7pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Characterization and Testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate tools like SEM, EDX, Optical Microscopy, XRD for defect identification, library maintenance, correlation of defects to Ic &amp;amp; mechanical properties of the product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out sample preparation techniques like selective etching, cross section polishing, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform destructive testing techniques like simple peel, cross hatch peel, 90-degree peel, transport Ic, electromechanical property tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Process Engineering Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands on support to process engineers in performing Department of Energy’s (DOE) and tracking/tracing product flow, collecting samples, testing and documenting results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform Statistical data analysis on the information collected from the Department of Energy (DOE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in root cause analysis, articulate and perform Hypothesis testing, document results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Operations on disposition decisions, process changes, sample collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow through and verify operational accuracy when performing experiments, new process deployments, new product routings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data Management &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the existing systems to collect, articulate, summarize and present to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formulate defect tracking dashboards and build the trends. Correlate to process metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and publish Failure Analysis (FA) reports, technical documentation, standard operating procedures (SOP&#39;s), work instructions (WI&#39;s) as development progresses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams, including production, quality, and maintenance, to support ongoing projects and resolve technical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in safety meetings and training sessions to understand and adhere to MetOx’s operational standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend project meetings, provide regular updates on process initiatives, and share insights to contribute to the team’s success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree program in Chemical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Industrial Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
