&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empower Your Future: &lt;/strong&gt;At MetOx International, we’re pioneering the next era of energy security and abundance through breakthrough superconducting technology. As a Quality Technician II, you’ll join a dynamic team committed to strengthening the world’s energy systems to make them more resilient, efficient, and reliable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at our global headquarters in Houston, TX, Quality Technician II performs advanced quality inspections and testing on raw materials, components, and finished goods, and takes the lead in identifying and documenting nonconforming material. This role supports quality investigations, root cause analysis, and may assist in training entry-level technicians. Ensures proper documentation and contributes to continuous improvement activities. Works under moderate supervision with increased autonomy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quality Control Testing and Measurement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts measurements and inspections on incoming raw materials and components to ensure they meet specified quality standards&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains batch house chemical inventory and ensures only qualified and verified materials are available for use in production&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Records and reports any non-conformities in critical materials received&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs verifications as necessary for each test, measurement, and monitoring device or equipment used&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receives and tracks production coupons and samples into the test laboratory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs product quality release tests and report any failed results&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adheres to all safety and health regulations as required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Testing Support for Engineering and R&amp;amp;D&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports Engineering teams by performing laboratory tests and measurements on supplied samples and delivering on-time results&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uses eQMS and LIMS electronic systems to report individual test results&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepares testing and measuring data packages and reports as requested&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Final Inspection and Final Quality Package Assembly&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts final inspections on products before release to ensure they meet the required quality standards&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assembles the final product package, including all necessary documentation, to accompany finished goods&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Audits, Verifications, and Inspections&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs laboratory and shop-floor scoped verification activities to ensure procedures and QMS processes are being followed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participates in internal audits of testing activities and of our QMS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly audits all measurement tools and gauges to ensure they are properly calibrated and verified for use&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of experience in lab technician, quality control, analyst, or engineering roles in a manufacturer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
