&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empower Your Future: &lt;/strong&gt;At MetOx International, we’re pioneering the next era of energy security and abundance through breakthrough superconducting technology. As a Research &amp;amp; Development (R&amp;amp;D) Technician, you’ll join a dynamic team committed to strengthening the world’s energy systems to make them more resilient, efficient, and reliable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at our global headquarters in Houston, TX, the R&amp;amp;D Technician supports the operation, development, and continuous improvement of MetOx’s advanced superconducting wire manufacturing and lamination processes. This role supports R&amp;amp;D, process scale-up, MOCVD development activities, equipment operation, process documentation, quality testing, and experimental execution within a fast-paced research and development environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The R&amp;amp;D Technician works closely with scientists, engineers, and manufacturing teams to support next-generation HTS technology development and manufacturing readiness activities. The ideal candidate is hands-on, detail-oriented, and comfortable supporting evolving technologies, equipment, and processes within a rapidly scaling technical environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process &amp;amp; Equipment Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operates and supports pilot-scale manufacturing and equipment used in the development of HTS wire and related processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with setup, operation, monitoring, and shutdown of R&amp;amp;D and process equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports execution of experimental trials, process development activities, and engineering evaluations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains safe and organized operation of laboratory, pilot line, and process areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with equipment troubleshooting, maintenance, and basic repairs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Procedure Development
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops, updates, and maintains standard operating procedures (SOPs), work instructions, and process documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documents process observations, deviations, and troubleshooting findings to support engineering analysis and continuous improvement efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with data collection, organization, and reporting on MOCVD development programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports continuous improvement of documentation practices to improve process consistency, repeatability, and manufacturing readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Control &amp;amp; Testing Support
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports operation of quality control and characterization equipment used to evaluate process and product performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with sample preparation, measurement collection, and documentation activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helps maintain calibration, organization, and readiness of QC equipment and testing areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports engineers and scientists by providing accurate and timely process and test data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous Improvement &amp;amp; Technical Support
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with root cause investigations, corrective actions, and process optimization activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports development, fabrication, and assembly of fixtures, tooling, and experimental components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborates cross-functionally with R&amp;amp;D, Manufacturing, Engineering, and Quality teams to support program objectives and technology development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports additional operational, technical, and facility-related activities as needed within a rapidly growing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
